value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the posterior inferior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum. It is part of the pIP-g cluster (Ren et al., 2016).

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron that develops from the first intermediate neural progenitor to form from neuroblast DM5 during the larval stage (Ren et al., 2016). There are 2 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010; Ren et al., 2016) and they are part of the pIP-g cluster (Ren et al., 2016).
A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM1.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DM1 (Ren et al., 2016) and has its cell body in the posterior medial protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately 21 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010; Ren et al., 2016).
A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM2.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DM2 (Ren et al., 2016) and has its cell body in the posterior medial protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Ren et al. (2016) find only 9 pMP-b cells per hemisphere in the DM2 lineage, whereas Cachero et al. (2010) report 22 female pMP-b cells. Cachero et al. (2010) unclear whether this or pMP-a maps to Yu et al. (2010) pMP5 - images look like pMP5 is pMP-b.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM4.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that has its cell body in the posterior medial protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately 12 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) report around 12 cells per cluster in males and females, but only 2 cells belong to the DM3 lineage according to Ren et al. (2016).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the posterior brain (Cachero et al., 2010). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010). It has arborization in the ipsilateral posterior lateral protocerebrum and anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Arborization regions determined from Cachero et al. (2010) data in Virtual Fly Brain.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior medial protocerebrum.

definition.value: Ren et al. (2016) identify the DM4-derived female equivalent of the male pMP-e (P1) neurons and note that the female pMP-e clone in Cachero et al. (2010) may be a misidentified unrelated clone. Unlike in the male, there does not appear to be overlap between dsx pC1 and fru pMP-e in the female (Ren et al., 2016).

value.value: Adult fruitless pMP-e neuron of the female. It develops from the DM4 neuroblast (Ren et al., 2016). There are approximately 7 of these cells per hemisphere (Ren et al., 2016). Many of them project upwards to innervate the superior medial protocerebrum (Ren et a., 2016).

definition.value: Ren et al. (2016) identify the DM4-derived female equivalent of the male pMP-e (P1) neurons and note that the female pMP-e clone in Cachero et al. (2010) may a be misidentified unrelated clone. Unlike in the male, there does not appear to be overlap between dsx pC1 and fru pMP-e in the female (Ren et al., 2016).

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM6.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DM6 (Ren et al., 2016) and has its cell body in the posterior medial protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately 20 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010; Ren et al., 2016).
Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the posterior brain (Cachero et al., 2010). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion. It contains around 5-6 neurons and it is not sexually dimorphic (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the lateral subesophageal zone (Cachero et al., 2010). It loops through the subesophageal zone and arborizes in the ipsilateral saddle (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately six of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Saddle arborization visualized from Cachero et al. (2010) data in Virtual Fly Brain.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion. It contains around 12 neurons and it is not sexually dimorphic (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the gnathal ganglion and arborization mainly in the ipsilateral dorsal subesophageal zone (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately 12 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the lateral subesophageal zone and arborization mainly in the saddle (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Saddle arborization visualized from Cachero et al. (2010) data in Virtual Fly Brain.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion. It contains around 8 neurons and it is not sexually dimorphic (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the ventral subesophageal zone (Cachero et al., 2010). It projects dorsally, then turns laterally to arborize in a lateral inferior region of the brain (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) show medial somas, so unclear if these are unpaired cells, i.e. 8 cells per brain or 8 cells per hemisphere.

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the ventral subesophageal zone (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) show a medial soma, so unclear if it is unpaired, i.e. 1 cell per brain or 1 cell per hemisphere.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPpd1.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DPLc1 (SMPpd1) (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately six of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPpl1.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DPLl1 (SLPpl1) (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 19 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the posterior superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010). Its arbors are mainly found in the ipsilateral superior lateral protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Arborization regions determined from Cachero et al. (2010) data in Virtual Fly Brain.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. Neurites form a local arbor and then project dorsally.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located ventrolaterally in the ventrolateral protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010). It forms a local arbor and then projects dorsally (Yu et al., 2010).

definition.value: Yu et al. (2010) did not find any male examples of this cell type.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DPLal2 (LHl2).

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the posterior superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHp2.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the posterior superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately three of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl3.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the posterior superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately two of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located dorsomedial to the antennal lobe. Neurites project bilaterally terminating with granular arborizations in the medial subesophageal zone and in the ipsilateral dorsal medial protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located dorsomedial to the antennal lobe (Yu et al., 2010). It has ipsilateral arbors in the dorsal medial protocerebrum and bilateral axonal arborization in the subesophageal zone (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located ventrolateral to the antennal lobe, usually away from the neuropil. Neurites project dorsally, fasciculating with the mediolateral antennal lobe tract until the fan-shaped body. It then makes a lateral dorsal turn. Neurites form web-like arborizations, likely to be axonal in the ipsi- and contralateral in the posterior region of the superior lateral and intermediate protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located ventral lateral to the antennal lobe (Yu et al., 2010). It projects dorsally, via the mediolateral antennal lobe tract until reaching the fan-shaped body, before making a lateral dorsal turn (Yu et al., 2010). Neurites form web-like arborizations, likely to be axonal in the ipsi- and contralateral posterior superior medial protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010).

definition.value: Yu et al. (2010) note that this is similar to TRPA1-expressing neurons in Hamada et al. (2008) - FBrf0205189.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located medioventral to the antennal lobe. A neurite projects through the esophageal foramen posteriorly then ipsilaterally to form axonal arbors in the anterior dorsal region of the lobula. There is also arborization in the posterior brain.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located medial ventral to the antennal lobe (Yu et al., 2010). It projects through the esophageal foramen posteriorly then forms axonal arbors in the anterior dorsal region of the ipsilateral lobula (Yu et al., 2010). There is also arborization in the posterior brain (Yu et al., 2010). It develops from the BAmv2 (PSa1) neuroblast (Ito et al., 2013).

definition.value: Yu et al. (2010) note that this type is similar to OA-AL2i2 from Busch et al. (2009) - FBrf0207458.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located medially, between the antennal lobe and the subesophageal zone. A neurite forms dense bilateral arbors in the antennal lobe and the subesophageal zone. A major neurite exits the brain via the posterior subesophageal zone to terminate in the pro-, meso, and metathoracic neuromeres.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. Neurites innervates a thin region in the lateral crescent.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located in the ventral region of the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. Neurites terminate in the ventrolateral protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma located on the surface of the ventrolateral protocerebrum and arborization in the ventrolateral protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior inferior protocerebrum. Neurites project posteromedially arborizing in the superior intermediate and medial protocerebrum, and a discrete region at the medial terminal of the mushroom gamma lobes in both hemispheres.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum. Neurites enter a tract in the medial posterior brain and project anteriorly behind the mushroom body lobes. The projections are likely to terminate in the lateral crescent and medial ring.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).
